---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const effective = 'June 16, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — elect-rix.tech"
  description="Terms governing use of the elect-rix.tech website and the basis on which information and research artifacts are provided."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        These terms govern your use of this website. They are written to be read, not to hide things.
        By using this site you agree to them.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-text-muted">Effective date: {effective}</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Who -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Who Operates This Site</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        This website (elect-rix.tech) is operated by <strong class="text-text">RixBot Technologies Inc.</strong>,
        a New Brunswick corporation, carrying on business as <strong class="text-text">elect-rix Technology
        Solutions</strong>. "We", "us", and "our" refer to RixBot Technologies Inc.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Informational -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Information Is Provided for General Purposes</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Content on this site — including articles, research artifacts, audits, advisories, checklists, and any
        "telemetry" or vendor reports — is provided for <strong class="text-text">general informational purposes
        only</strong>. It reflects our analysis as of its stated date and the sources available to us at that time.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        It is <strong class="text-text">not</strong> legal, financial, security-certification, or professional
        advice, and it is <strong class="text-text">not</strong> a certified audit, accreditation, or guarantee.
        Where a report assesses a third-party product or vendor, our findings are observations and questions to
        verify — not legal conclusions about that party's conduct. Always verify independently before acting.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- No warranty -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. No Warranty</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        This site and its content are provided <strong class="text-text">"as is" and "as available"</strong>,
        without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including accuracy, completeness, fitness for a
        particular purpose, or non-infringement. We work to keep information correct and current but do not warrant
        that it is free of errors or omissions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Limitation -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, RixBot Technologies Inc. is not liable for any loss or damage
        arising from your use of, or reliance on, this site or its content. Nothing here creates a consulting
        engagement, advisory relationship, or duty of care. A professional relationship arises only under a
        separate written agreement signed by both parties.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- IP -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        The elect-rix name, logo, site design, text, and original research artifacts are the property of RixBot
        Technologies Inc. and protected under Canadian law. You may read, link to, and quote brief excerpts with
        attribution. You may not republish substantial portions, present our work as your own, or use our brand in
        a way that implies endorsement, without written permission.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Third party -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. Third-Party Names and Links</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        References to third-party companies, products, or trademarks are for identification and commentary only and
        remain the property of their respective owners. Such references do not imply affiliation or endorsement in
        either direction. We are not responsible for the content of external sites we link to.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Acceptable use -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-text-muted list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Do not attempt to disrupt, attack, or gain unauthorized access to the site or its infrastructure.</li>
        <li>Do not scrape or reproduce content for resale or to misrepresent its origin.</li>
        <li>Do not use the site for any unlawful purpose.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Governing law -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">8. Governing Law</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        These terms are governed by the laws of the Province of New Brunswick and the federal laws of Canada
        applicable therein. Any dispute is subject to the courts of New Brunswick. There are no offshore
        arbitration clauses.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Changes -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">9. Changes</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We may revise these terms as needed. The effective date above reflects the current version. Continued use
        of the site after changes constitutes acceptance.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="mb-4 p-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:hello@elect-rix.tech" class="text-accent-bright hover:underline">hello@elect-rix.tech</a><br />
        RixBot Technologies Inc. (operating as elect-rix Technology Solutions), New Brunswick, Canada.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="text-center text-sm text-text-muted font-medium pt-8">
      elect-rix.tech &#x2014; Integrity. Loyalty. Honesty. &#x2014; Tested.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
